ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.
M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: Sample description: tissue type, i.e. blood, saliva, brain etc.
ValueRange: whole blood; saliva; brain; urine; serum; plasma; CSF; IPS; Fibroblast; Neuronal Progenitor; skin biopsy; temporal cortex; lymphoblastoid cell line; unknown; semen; frontal cortex; parietal cortex; basal ganglia; Placenta; hair; occipital visual cortex; cerebellum; spleen; stool; muscle; kidney; liver; heart; cord blood; nasal swab; DNA; RNA; breastmilk; buccal; oral cells; rectal swab; cervicovaginal swab

ElementDescription: dbGaP; NDAR; NIMH Genetics; AGRE; Sfari; Proteomics DB name
Sample provider: i.e. NIMH_Genetics; ATP; Correil
Miscellaneous comments on study, interview, methodology relevant to this form data
Sample preparation batch OR DNA/RNA Isolation batch OR experimental batch
Make and model of Mass Spectroscopy Instrument used to collect the data
Name and version number of the software used to collect the data
Name and version number of the software used to analyze the data
Name and version number of the software used to perform statistical analysis on the results
Lambda DNA spike-in concentration in ng
Library ID as provided by the lab
If the library is paired-end or single-end

ElementDescription: Total number of bases covered by ATAC-seq reads/size of genome
Number of cells or nuclei sequenced
Number of PCR cycles to amplify transposased DNA fragments
The strand from which the read originates in a strand-specific protocol
A set of references (e.g., canonical assembled contigs) which defines a common coordinate space for comparing reference-aligned experimental data
Total number of sequencing reads from a library
The technology used to generate the data in this file
Fluorescent color labeling for an array
Control samples suitable for normalization and batch correction
The maximum length of the read
The minimum length of the read
Indicates whether or not the bisulfiteSeq library is directional
Whether or not the library is stranded.
The hybridization batch the sample was in
TMT channel the sample is labeled with
